abstract.text: An object that describes a user’s participation in a share.

inlineContent.text: Participants are a key element of sharing in CloudKit. A participant provides information about an iCloud user and their participation in a share, including their identity, acceptance status, permissions, and role.
The acceptance status determines the participant’s visibilty of the shared records. Statuses are:
to accept the share. Upon acceptance, CloudKit makes the shared records available in the participant’s shared database. The records remain accessible for as long as the participant’s status is

Participants with write permissions can modify or delete any record that you include in the share. However, only the owner can delete a shared hierarchy’s root record. If a participant attempts to delete the share, CloudKit removes the participant. The share remains active for all other participants.
